## Features:

### Installation & Updates
- Automatically installs Legacy Console Edition on first launch
- Checks for updates every time you open the launcher - downloads and installs only if a newer version is available and with user confirmation. 
- Supports both the *game* and the *dedicated server*
- Dedicated server does not auto install***

### Launching
- Launch the game directly from the launcher once installed
- The launch button is always visible — active when the game is installed, greyed out when it isn't

## Files that aren't touched during updating:

### Game:
- World saves
- Settings.dat
- uid.dat
- Options.txt
- username.txt

### Dedicated Server:
- banned-ips.json
- banned-players.json
- server.properties
- whitelist.json
- server.db

## Custom Install Location:
- Choose where to install the game on first run
- Choose where to install the server (if you want to install the server too)
- The launcher remembers your chosen location(s)
- Default: `%AppData%\.Minecraft Consoles` / `%AppData%\.Minecraft Consoles Server`
- Open either folder directly from the launcher with one click

### Server Properties Editor
    Edit these server settings from inside the launcher without touching any config files manually:

## Server Setup:
| Setting | Description |
|---|---|
| Whitelist | Restrict who can join |
| Server IP | IP address to bind to |
| Server Port | Port the server listens on (default 25565) |
| LAN Advertise | Broadcast server on local network |
| Spawn Protection | Radius around spawn that non-ops can't break (0–64) |
| World Size | classic / small / medium / large |

## Gameplay:
| Setting | Description |
|---|---|
| Bonus Chest | Spawn a bonus chest on world creation |
| Fire Spreads | Whether fire spreads to nearby blocks |
| Keep Inventory | Keep items on death |
| Generate Structures | Spawn villages, dungeons etc. |
| Mob Griefing | Whether mobs can break/modify blocks |
| Difficulty | Peaceful / Easy / Normal / Hard |
| Gamemode | Survival / Creative |
| Max Players | Maximum concurrent players (up to 8) |
